#title()[gDNA extraction protocol]

\

= _Harvesting fibroblasts_

Aspirate the existing media and add 3mL of dPBS to each 6-cm. dish to wash. After you aspirate the dPBS, add 1 mL of TrypLE per dish and incubate for 1 minute. Once the cells are detached, carefully aspirate the TrypLE and use 1 mL of fibroblast media to collect the cells. Wash down any remaining cells with another mL of fibroblast media, then centrifuge at 300 _g_ for 5 minutes at room temperature to pellet the cells.

= _gDNA extraction_

Use the ThermoFisher Genomic DNA mini-kit (K182007) to extract the gDNA. If using the kit for the first time, first add 15 mL of 100% ethanol to the bottle of wash buffer \#1, and 17.5 mL to wash buffer \#2.

Otherwise, proceed by preparing your PBS (via pellet in MilliQ water) and resuspending the cell pellet in 200 $mu$L of PBS, gently pipetting up and down to homogenize. Prepare a 1.5-mL tube per pellet with 10 $mu$L Proteinase K, then transfer your 200 $mu$L of cell suspension. Add 20 $mu$L of RNAse A to each tube, then vortex for 5 seconds to homogenize before incubating for 2 minutes at room temperature. Next, add 200 $mu$L of lysis/binding buffer to each tube and vortex for 5 seconds, then incubate for 10 minutes at 55$degree$C. Finally, add 200 $mu$L of 100% ethanol to each tube and vortex for 5 seconds.

Prepare one spin column and collection tube per 1.5-mL tube. Transfer \~600 $mu$L of each lysate to its corresponding spin column, maintaining the same volume across samples, then centrifuge the columns for 1 minute at 10,000 _g_ at room temperature (18--22$degree$C). Transfer each spin column to a new collection tube.

In the new collection tube(s), add 500 $mu$L of wash buffer \#1 (with ethanol) to each volumn, then centrifuge for 1 minute at 10,000 _g_ at room temperature. Transfer each spin column to a new tube again and add 500 $mu$L of wash buffer \#2 (with ethanol) to each column; this time, centrifuge for 3 minutes at max. speed (20,000 _g_) at room temperature.

Transfer each spin column to a new collection tube once more. This time, add 50 $mu$L of elution buffer to each column and incubate for 1 minute at room temperature before centrifuging at 1.5 minutes at max. speed (20,000 _g_) at room temperature. You can measure the gDNA concentration and quality using the Nanodrop (choose "dsDNA"; drop 1 $mu$L of nuclease-free water for the blank, then clean with a KimWipe and add 1 $mu$L per sample, cleaning in between). If necessary, dilute the concentration to \<100 ng/$mu$L. If you need, you can recover more gDNA by eluting again. Transfer the full volumes (\~50 $mu$L) to new 1.5-mL tubes and record the volumes. You can then store them at -20 or -80$degree$C, or proceed to the PCR.

= _PCR_

To run your PCR, first prepare PCR mixes for your samples (GoTaq G2 Hot Start Green Master Mix with your forward and reverse primers in nuclease-free water). Add 23 $mu$L of your mixes to their respective 8-strip PCR tubes, then 2 $mu$L of each gDNA sample to their respective tubes. Vortex the strips for 3 seconds, then spin down for 30 seconds in the mini-centrifuge. Using the ThermoCycler, run the PCR program, then remove the tubes and place them in the -4$degree$C.

= _Gel electrophoresis_

First, pour your agarose gel by making the agarose solution and molding around the wellcomb. Place your gel in the unit and fill with 1X TAE buffer to cover. You can then load 5 $mu$L of your ladder (BenchTop PCR marker) and 10 $mu$L of your samples. Run at 150V for 30 minutes, then image using the ChemiDoc imager.